text.__SUMMARY__: Eucalyptus staeri, commonly known as Albany blackbutt, is a Eucalyptus tree that is native to Western Australia.
text.Description: E staeri will grow to a height of 2 metres (7 ft) to 15 m (49 ft) and has rough bark that is fissured longitudinally. It blooms between October and November producing circular white fine  flowers.
text.Range: It is found mostly in the south west corner of the Great Southern region of Western Australia centred around the town of  Albany with smaller populations extending north into the Wheatbelt. The preferred habitat is sandy soil in coastal scrub.
